summary: What jobs do you want the kids to have when they grow up?
question: What jobs do you want the kids to have when they grow up?
answer:
I think Andi would have a pretty good shot at a career in fashion. She’s good at designing accessories and her style is on point.

Cyrus would probably be a writer/filmmaker.

Buffy would be a good gym coach at a school or for a small sports team.

Jonah would take after Bowie and teach music. Maybe open up his own music store.

TJ would be a social worker.

Amber would be a dancer.

question: Please sir more dumbass trio
answer:
Dumbass trio: part one, part two, part three, part four, part five, part six, part seven, part eight, part nine, part ten, part eleven

- Once were playing catch in the park and managed to hit a wasp nest with their ball. Had to run for their lives. Ended up jumping in a pond to avoid getting stung.

- Tried to bake Andi a birthday cake and forgot the flour. The result was just a very sugary omelette. They didn’t have time to make another one so they just iced it, stuck candles on the top and hoped she wouldn’t notice.

- She noticed.

- They had to stay up late to do some last minute panic studying once so Marty created this horrible concoction of five hour energies, energy drinks, soda and coffee. They were all pretty incoherent after drinking it and Jonah claims he met God that night.

- On Marty and Buffy’s first date, Jonah and TJ hid in the back of the diner with sunglasses and hoods on watching and coaching Marty by text.

- Buffy knew they were there. They freaked out the waiters.

- Marty fell off the roof of his house trying to retrieve a frisbee but it’s okay because Jonah broke his fall.

- All three of them are banned from the local Starbucks and won’t tell anyone why.

- You think it’s bad when TJ raps? Imagine all three of these idiots rapping in unison. It’s awful. Buffy calls them the knock-off Beastie Boys.

body: Imagine everyone is at lunch and Cyrus is sitting there eating a bag of chips when TJ climbs on top of the table, grabs a bouquet of daisies that Andi handed him and says “Cyrus, it would make my daisy if you went to prom with me maybe?” which makes Cyrus almost chokes on a chip before nodding and getting up to hug him. He couldn’t believe after all these years he finally got the courage to do something like that.
